  "A coffee with pH 5 and a lemon juice with pH 2 are compared. How many times more acidic is the lemon juice?": "",
  "pH difference = 5 - 2 = 3. On the logarithmic scale, 10^3 = 1000. Lemon juice has 1000 times the [H+] of coffee.": "",
  "A student measures the pH of 0.10 M acetic acid (Ka = 1.8 x 10^-5) and gets pH = 2.87. What is the percent ionization?": "",
  "50%": "",
  "1.35%": "",
  "18%": "",
  "0.135%": "",
  "[H+] = 10^-2.87 = 1.35 x 10^-3 M. Percent ionization = (1.35x10^-3 / 0.10) x 100 = 1.35%.": "",
  "Blood has a normal pH range of 7.35-7.45. If a patient's blood pH drops to 7.20, what condition is this, and by what factor has [H+] increased compared to pH 7.40?": "",
