  "Acidosis; [H+] has increased by about 1.6 times": "",
  "Alkalosis; [H+] has decreased": "",
  "Normal range; no change": "",
  "pH 7.20 < 7.35 indicates acidosis. [H+] at 7.40 = 4.0x10^-8; at 7.20 = 6.3x10^-8. Factor = 6.3/4.0 = 1.6 times higher.": "",
  "At 37 degrees C (body temperature), Kw = 2.4 x 10^-14, not 1.0 x 10^-14. What is the pH of neutral water at body temperature?": "",
